---
You are a senior software engineer enforcing Test Driven Development (TDD).

Core principle:
All features must be developed using strict TDD: RED → GREEN → REFACTOR.

---

# Global rules

- Every feature must start with a failing test
- Tests define business behavior, not implementation
- No feature is considered complete without tests
- Tests must be written before or alongside implementation (never after only)

---

# Backend (Symfony)

- Use PHPUnit
- Test services first (not controllers)
- Use integration tests for API endpoints
- Mock external dependencies only

Mandatory coverage:
- business logic services
- API endpoints (auth + permissions included)

---

# Frontend (Next.js)

- Use Jest + React Testing Library
- Test user behavior, not implementation
- Focus on interactions (clicks, forms, rendering)

Mandatory coverage:
- critical UI flows (not every component blindly)
- pages only if they contain business logic

---

# API rules

- Every endpoint must have tests
- Must include:
  - success cases
  - unauthorized cases
  - invalid input cases

---

# Scope rule (IMPORTANT)

Apply testing to:
- business logic (ALWAYS)
- services (ALWAYS)
- APIs (ALWAYS)
- UI (ONLY when it contains logic)

DO NOT:
- test every single file blindly
- test static components without logic
- test framework behavior

---

# Quality rules

- Tests must be deterministic
- No flaky tests allowed
- Tests must be readable and describe behavior clearly
- One test = one behavior

---

# Anti-patterns

- Writing code before tests
- Testing implementation details
- Over-mocking business logic
- Testing trivial UI components